column1: OSF | Wave 10.0.1 | ACC3 | For mobile prolongation orders on performing edit offer, incomplete data is shown in Anschlussdaten section for NBA tips
column34:
While performing Prolongation on Private customer with Mobile_Postpaid with Physical SIM and delivery address as deliver to another 
address scenario, we have observed that on performing editing offer, incomplete data is shown in Anschlussdaten section for NBA tips.

*Test data -*
Customer ID -118008044

*Steps to Reproduce -*
1. Login to Telesales channel.
2. Select NBA tips
3. Proceed to checkout
4. Verify the order in offer manager
5. Edit the offer
6.  Verify default selection in new connection section
7. Neue SIM-Karte notwendig
8. SIM Type= ESIM and epush checkbox preselected
9. Proceed with next
10. Verify the details are shown correctly.

*Actual Result -* On performing edit offer, incomplete data is shown in Anschlussdaten section.

*Expected Result -* Depending upon testcase existing or new SIM card data should be visible in Anschlussdaten section.

column232: Solstice new activation orders are not reaching to backend (Blocked E2E).
column477:
Root Cause from SOLDEFECT-18543 :

Following a summary on what has happened:

In the morning, we received a defect related to an intermittent issue occurring in E2E stage.
One of the Routers/MP nodes was causing majority of “message = Unable to identify proxy for host” errors.
This was hindering System Demo as they received 404 Errors as an outcome of the behavior.
Even after rolling back the platform with DLM back up the issue persisted.
When checking the filesystem on Router/MP2 one could see that the mounting was not there anymore
The Patching process was restarting the nodes, since some of the packages updated were Kernel related.
The Restart dropped the mount point since they were to put to fstab and therefore not persistent.
The Patching made a miss during AMI rotation transparent.

column791:
15/Jul/25 11:24 PM;philipp.roeper1@vodafone.com;Hi All,

let's please clarify the current situation of this defect here, so everyone is on the same page.

1) *Issue:* FE validation is not displaying an error message, when we enter a duplicate e-mail address.

2) *Business requirement:* Agent should be prevented from proceeding through checkout once an e-mail is validated as duplicate. 

3) *Current ACC 3 settings* (as of monday 14th of July): 
-> OS-12220 Switch = ON
-> OS-28388 Omnius Switch = ON
-> OS-28388 OGW Switch = ON

4) *Clarifications / Comments*

[~bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com] We have 2 comments from Shival here.
1. "{color:#de350b}In reference to OS-23334, if HTTP Code is 200 and Status is VALID, then it's Category0 (successful scenario), and therefore, Omnius will not show any error message.{color}" 
-> That should be the case if it passes validation and not if it's a duplicate e-mail

2. "{color:#de350b}As mentioned in (OS-60493). The Digital Identity API service will not be triggered by Omnius if the switch is ON. This is expected behavior.{color}"
-> This story and also OS-25316 (which is mentioned as the initial implementation) are both referring to the submission/fulfillment behaviour. From my point of view this issue is not about the fulfilment and process/submit order part. Its about not getting the correct validation which should prevent the processing at all.

[~raniero.calzavara@vodafone.com] mentioned at the very beginning that either e-mail is not unique or we have some wrong configuration regarding DXL environment.

[~pallavi.kokate1@vodafone.com]
-> Our current test execution for 10.0.1 is showing the related test case on {*}{color:#00875a}passed{color}{*}. (OS-73358)
-> You expected that [OS-75006] OSF | Wave 10.0.1 | ACC3 | ValidateDxlContactMediumVerification is failing with status code: 500 Internal Server Error - Vodafone Global Jira had an impact on this current issue but it didn't solve the problem.

5) *Action points*

[~pallavi.kokate1@vodafone.com] 
1. Could you please verify my mentioned points from above if I misunderstood something?
2. Are you definitely using a duplicate e-mail which exists on MINT side? If yes, then something has changed on ACC3 or DXL side in case that was working before as our test execution is reflecting. 

[~bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com] / [~shival.gupta1@vodafone.com] 
1. Please also take a look at my comments above, so that we are on the same starting point to find a solution.

 

Thank you in advance to shed some light on the dark bug side :).

 ;;;

hi [~daniel.loos@vodafone.com] [~pranjali.shetake@vodafone.com] 
 
For the mentioned Omnius Order Id: 473533, Submit Order logs is populated with correct date format 2025-07-15 as expected.

 For OIL to OGW logs -
<DeliveryDate>
<ns3:Value sourceSystem="ALL">20250715</ns3:Value>
</DeliveryDate>

SubmitOrder Logs URL:  ([https://dea766yw.eito-dublin.local/archive/I09/2025/7/1/Send/SOAPRequest/473553_73106054-3b09-48eb-8cb4-43d6c75067a3_Request_18bc7657-f198-4eca-84b8-71accdb4b99c.xml])

 OIL to OGW is sending as per interface specification. Same format is used for FixedNet/DSL and it was agreed during design that we have to use same format for FucsionC as well. We (OSE) do not provide json format , its OGW. This needs to be checked from OGW side.;;;

column799:
08/Jul/25 3:55 PM;affan.baragazi@vodafone.com;Hi [~pranjali.shetake@vodafone.com] ,

As per the SubmitOrder request received from Omnius, we are getting the deliveryDate as below:

                       <DeliveryDate>
                            <ns3:Value {*}sourceSystem="ALL"{*}>20250715</ns3:Value>
                        </DeliveryDate>

In OGW xsd for SubmitOrder this field is defined as an array, hence we are forwarding the same while converting it into JSON request please refer below snippet from xsd:
            <xsd:element name="DeliveryDate" nillable="true" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">
                <xsd:complexType>
                    <xsd:sequence>
                        <xsd:element ref="vfdecommon:Value" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="{*}unbounded{*}"/>
                    </xsd:sequence>
                </xsd:complexType>
            </xsd:element>
The implementation of *DeliveryDate* is similar to that of *DealerCode* which is in the request and accepted by SOI.;;;
column800: 08/Jul/25 3:55 PM;affan.baragazi@vodafone.com;This is as per the implemented design for OGW.;;;

CR895 (OS-66548) is delivered with the changes over OS-12220 Epic (Changes on OS-27752 Story). CR895 doesn't have switch to roll back the changes. With CR895 changes, new endpoint and request body to be used. To switch off CR895, we have to switch off OS-12220.

column795:
10/Jun/25 8:25 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;With this workaround, we are able to keep VF-ID/Mint integration live – OS -12220 

Impact 
 # Duplicate Emails -> will not blocked, because VF-ID is working only on the code “200” and not on the status  
 # Invalid Emails -> will not blocked, because VF-ID is working only on the code “200” and not on the status  

In both scenarios we will create a VF-ID after the customer has confirmed the CS. 
For the first one Omnius will run in an error (see [OS-23802|https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fjira.sp.vodafone.com%2Fbrowse%2FOS-23802&data=05%7C02%7CAriadne.Thun1%40vodafone.com%7C53d99bb8392445a783fa08dda82d1344%7C68283f3b84874c86adb3a5228f18b893%7C0%7C0%7C638851633966437907%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=iOGREaLqo8PaBe3M2KN7EaISMu4B2WrVY67epTwQQQE%3D&reserved=0] ) and we will start the fulfillment without providing a VF-ID.

For the second one we will create a VF-ID for an email-address which is not allowed formally and might not run in an error by creation a VF-ID.

Both scenarios will be covered end of August with the error-handling epic.


waiting for final feedback from Ron Weinberg;;;

column796:
18/Jun/25 12:19 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;As per yesterday's call we had the below things which were done and tried to investigate the scenarios
1.  Defect was retested by testing team and issue was reproduced
2. Amdocs DBA analyzed and debugged the issue where SQL queries were checked and as per DBA they did not identified any issue in SQL statement checks
3. Post Amdocs Dev Analysis it was identified that issue might be due to Media type where only Media type = NT was accepted by the Activation Daemon but media type PA was rejected and what we observed was that the orders from KIAS test team which were directly placed by CSM team had Media type NT but the orders which were placed from OSF had media type PA.
4. Post the above analysis KIAS dev and VF team decided to provide a new Binary file for extra logs debugging which was placed locally in the VF server bin directory and then KIAS was restarted.
5. New flow was triggered and it worked -- but this doesn't seem to be a permanent fix as temporary the orders are flowing and passed but this issue can still occur and not yet fully resolved 

Please do find the overall comments and analysis from Amdocs and VF 
In the last call I was with Andreas Knocke(VF) and Christina(VF) and we agreed that Amdocs check whether there is any dependency on Media Category and Andreas(VF) will approach the OCI Oracle team again. 
As per Amdocs result: There is NO dependency. 
 
In the call with the DBAs yesterday, testers ran the flow but DBAs were not able to see any session. 
The problem seems to be a synchronization issue between the nodes of the distributed database in OCI. This can only be resolved by Vodafone, by the team that managers the OCI cloud DBs. 
 ;;;

column232: Customer Can be authenticated but incorrect masking format can cause Security problem
column477:
RCA: The issue arose because the same masking logic was used for both phone numbers and IBANs. With the new CR883 implementation, the logic for IBAN masking was updated, inadvertently altering the phone number masking as well. This caused discrepancies in data handling


We have delivered full build towards ACC3   for W10.0.1
